summary:
The Security Council,
Recalling previous resolutions on Sudan,
Considering the Southern Sudan referendum results and the Government of Southern Sudan's request for a continued UN presence,
Determining the situation remains a threat to international peace and security,

1. Extends UNMIS mandate until 9 July 2011 as set out in resolution 1590 (2005);
2. Announces intent to establish a successor mission to UNMIS;
3. Requests the Secretary-General to consult with CPA parties and submit a report by 16 May;
4. Authorizes UNMIS to utilize assets to prepare for the successor mission;
5. Decides to remain seized of the matter.
